18:59.519 --> 19:01.386
Do... do you remember?

19:01.388 --> 19:02.820
Your first?

19:02.822 --> 19:04.188
Yeah, what the hell did I just say?

19:04.190 --> 19:06.090
Of course I...

19:10.130 --> 19:11.496
No.

19:11.498 --> 19:12.916
Maybe.

19:12.919 --> 19:15.733
Look, my point is this.

19:15.735 --> 19:18.770
That you just gotta hope

19:18.772 --> 19:22.907
that you did it for a reason.

19:22.909 --> 19:25.043
And I mean a good reason.

19:27.247 --> 19:30.281
And Hailey's a damn good reason.

19:30.283 --> 19:31.816
Can I tell you a secret?

19:31.818 --> 19:34.218
One I stinky pinky swore never to tell?

19:34.220 --> 19:35.337
What?

19:35.340 --> 19:37.655
When Hailey and I were
at the Sonny Shine show...

19:39.526 --> 19:41.059
The whole reason she snuck away

19:41.061 --> 19:42.897
was so Sonny could hear her wish.

19:43.778 --> 19:46.831
Her one wish she'd
waited her whole life.

19:49.739 --> 19:51.636
- Hailey's wish was...
- Hold that thought.

19:51.638 --> 19:53.771
I'm about to get a little road ragey.

19:53.773 --> 19:54.972
What the...

20:05.685 --> 20:08.119
I think we can agree
this one was not my fault.

20:16.629 --> 20:18.629
Officer, is there something wrong?

20:18.631 --> 20:22.200
What the hell are you
doing in Blue's car?

20:22.202 --> 20:24.535
You know, at a certain point,

20:24.537 --> 20:26.604
sticking your gun in my face,

20:26.606 --> 20:28.840
it's, you know... Kinda
loses its specialness.

20:28.842 --> 20:30.970
Laws of diminishing
returns and all that.

20:30.973 --> 20:32.357
I mean, you want me
to take you seriously,

20:32.359 --> 20:34.439
at some point you're gonna
have to pull that trigger.

20:35.482 --> 20:37.748
Aww, for crying out loud.

20:37.750 --> 20:39.984
Hey, hey, hey.

20:39.986 --> 20:43.321
Give me your keys, again.

20:43.323 --> 20:45.056
Let's do this.

20:45.058 --> 20:48.192
We get Blue, we get your kid.

20:48.194 --> 20:50.261
Listen to her, what is this we stuff?

20:50.263 --> 20:52.298
I didn't know, all right?

20:52.301 --> 20:54.232
There were a lot of things
I looked the other way,

20:54.234 --> 20:56.601
but the kids... I didn't know, Nick.

20:56.603 --> 20:59.170
You gotta fucking believe me. Nick?

20:59.172 --> 21:01.606
It's Amanda. Amanda?

21:01.608 --> 21:03.908
Merry, I'm in trouble.

21:03.910 --> 21:05.276
It's him, it's gotta be.

21:05.278 --> 21:06.428
Amanda, it's me.

21:06.431 --> 21:07.678
Where are you?

21:07.680 --> 21:10.715
Nick?

21:10.717 --> 21:13.084
He's got her, it's gotta be him.

21:13.086 --> 21:13.918
Who has her?

21:13.920 --> 21:15.553
Sonny Shine.

21:15.555 --> 21:17.006
She needs you.

21:17.009 --> 21:18.956
Amanda, listen to me.

21:18.958 --> 21:20.458
Amanda?

21:20.460 --> 21:21.572
Amanda?

21:22.672 --> 21:23.763
What the hell?

21:23.766 --> 21:25.141
What the hell's a Sonny Shine?

21:29.002 --> 21:30.998
He'd never hurt Hailey.

21:31.001 --> 21:33.137
He's got Shine Tower
58th and Lex, let's go.

21:33.139 --> 21:35.006
He doesn't live in a tower.

21:35.008 --> 21:37.308
Sonny lives in a
castle. I saw it myself.

21:37.310 --> 21:38.626
What, wait.

21:38.629 --> 21:39.695
What did you say?

21:39.698 --> 21:40.745
Hailey and I went there.

21:40.747 --> 21:41.646
Amanda took us.

21:41.648 --> 21:43.614
It was the best day ever.

21:43.616 --> 21:46.212
It's a great big building
with a great big gate.

21:46.215 --> 21:48.753
And there were lights,
and cameras, and...

21:48.755 --> 21:50.755
Lights and cameras?

21:55.828 --> 21:59.931
It was you.

21:59.933 --> 22:01.732
I didn't want it to be.

22:01.734 --> 22:05.236
I told myself lies not to believe it.

22:09.876 --> 22:13.678
Those spraytanned
apes were a disgrace...

22:13.680 --> 22:15.313
To apes.

22:15.315 --> 22:18.049
They threaded their eyebrows, Isa.

22:18.051 --> 22:21.009
They waxed their armpits.

22:21.012 --> 22:22.636
I needed gangsters,

22:22.639 --> 22:25.140
and you gave me Spandau Ballet.

22:27.780 --> 22:31.629
You think you know all the secrets?

22:31.631 --> 22:36.259
I have done things...

22:36.262 --> 22:41.772
Things that you couldn't
possibly imagine.

22:41.774 --> 22:43.360
I had no choice.

22:43.363 --> 22:45.409
But once I get that password,

22:45.411 --> 22:47.540
those days are over.

22:48.815 --> 22:51.148
I answer to no one.

22:53.686 --> 22:55.553
You gonna answer to that?

23:01.928 --> 23:03.794
I had a visit today

23:03.796 --> 23:06.197
from a mother looking for her daughter.

23:06.199 --> 23:08.342
I can give you eight good reasons

23:08.345 --> 23:09.800
why this makes me upset.

23:09.802 --> 23:11.798
I want them signed, sealed,

23:11.801 --> 23:14.538
and delivered tomorrow,
Christmas morning.

23:14.540 --> 23:16.240
And if they're not,

23:16.242 --> 23:18.709
it won't be me who gets exterminated!

23:23.116 --> 23:25.157
You came to me an unwashed,

23:25.160 --> 23:30.187
unkempt, motley assortment
of... God, who am I kidding?

23:30.189 --> 23:33.491
I cannot wait to get
rid of you petri dishes.

23:33.493 --> 23:36.861
Especially you.

23:36.863 --> 23:38.649
This is not the end of your journey,

23:38.652 --> 23:41.232
but the beginning, blah, blah, blah.

23:41.234 --> 23:43.901
You were plucked from obscurity
to serve a greater purpose,

23:43.903 --> 23:45.870
yadda, yadda, whatever.

23:45.872 --> 23:47.384
There were successes...

23:50.777 --> 23:52.977
And there were disasters.

23:55.014 --> 23:56.881
Congratulations, Kenji.

23:56.883 --> 24:00.251
You have achieved top
honors because you're Asian.

24:00.253 --> 24:02.553
And as a reward, you will go first.

24:02.555 --> 24:05.790
Your new parents will
be very, very proud,

24:05.792 --> 24:08.125
assuming you survive
the packaging process.

24:22.141 --> 24:24.241
Mister?

24:24.243 --> 24:26.210
What is it?

24:26.212 --> 24:28.879
I need to go to the bathroom.

24:28.881 --> 24:30.648
For God's sake.

24:30.650 --> 24:33.751
I told you to go before
we started packaging.

24:33.753 --> 24:36.120
Fine, go.

24:37.256 --> 24:39.557
There it is, Nick,

24:39.559 --> 24:41.737
home of the Rainbow Castle.

24:41.740 --> 24:42.927
Well, if that doesn't scream perv,

24:42.929 --> 24:44.362
I don't know what does.

24:44.365 --> 24:45.329
When I look at it,

24:45.331 --> 24:47.331
all I see is, "Let's play!"

24:47.333 --> 24:49.333
- Exactly.
- Look.

24:49.335 --> 24:52.503
Checking front entrance now.

24:52.505 --> 24:54.839
Is that normal for children's TV?

24:54.841 --> 24:56.941
You tell me, pops.

24:56.943 --> 24:58.342
Funny.

25:01.280 --> 25:03.581
All right, look,

25:03.583 --> 25:07.518
I gotta talk to this little, blue, um...

25:07.520 --> 25:08.819
Well, you keep saying that,

25:08.821 --> 25:11.088
but I've never seen one
with wings on its back

25:11.090 --> 25:12.423
and a thing coming out of it's...

25:12.425 --> 25:15.092
I mean, we call it a...

25:15.094 --> 25:16.660
Go on.

25:21.834 --> 25:23.434
All right, you, look at me.

25:23.436 --> 25:25.836
Happilocus Imaginus, Defender of Zork,

25:25.838 --> 25:27.326
First Knight of the Cupcake Kingdom,

25:27.329 --> 25:29.055
hero of the Frosting Wars.

25:29.058 --> 25:30.775
Reporting for duty, sir!

25:33.679 --> 25:36.881
She's counting on you.

25:36.883 --> 25:40.284
I'm counting on you.

25:40.286 --> 25:43.020
Go find Hailey.

25:45.825 --> 25:47.892
What?

25:57.371 --> 25:58.836
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah,

25:58.838 --> 25:59.832
all right, look.

25:59.842 --> 26:01.294
We got a big building here, so...

26:01.297 --> 26:02.199
Let's split up.

26:02.202 --> 26:03.409
I'll take the front.

26:03.412 --> 26:05.812
I'll take the back.

26:08.519 --> 26:09.647
You good?

26:09.649 --> 26:11.482
Yeah.

26:17.156 --> 26:18.681
You got this idea that your ex

26:18.684 --> 26:20.491
is some kind of wounded flower.

26:20.493 --> 26:23.145
Amanda's a goddamn pit bull,

26:23.148 --> 26:25.815
with one hell of a
right cross, by the way.

26:25.818 --> 26:27.331
She can take care of herself.

26:34.750 --> 26:36.341
Assunta, open the door.

26:39.812 --> 26:41.411
It's the Old Don's password.

26:41.414 --> 26:43.387
Mikey has it and he's
going to give it to Blue.

26:52.489 --> 26:53.588
Okay.

26:53.591 --> 26:54.591
Wait, what?

26:57.497 --> 26:59.597
Yes, yes, that's why we must stop him.

26:59.599 --> 27:00.731
Open the door, please.

27:03.603 --> 27:05.469
Okay, all right.

27:05.471 --> 27:08.038
Mamma...

27:10.209 --> 27:14.111
Nonna...

27:14.113 --> 27:18.649
Bisnonna...

27:18.651 --> 27:20.518
I should've never let
Mikey get on that plane.

27:20.520 --> 27:22.052
I just wanted him to have a good...

27:22.054 --> 27:23.587
Shh!

27:28.160 --> 27:29.426
No talisman.

27:38.604 --> 27:40.938
Hee.

27:40.940 --> 27:42.840
Talisman.

27:44.944 --> 27:50.080
So, as the thread weaves a tapestry

27:50.082 --> 27:52.917
of space and time,

27:52.919 --> 27:55.920
so does your brother's soul

27:55.922 --> 27:57.821
unwind.

28:00.526 --> 28:03.260
That is not a talisman.

28:03.262 --> 28:06.430
That is a ball of yarn.

28:06.432 --> 28:07.665
Talisman.

28:07.667 --> 28:09.315
That is a cat toy.

28:09.318 --> 28:10.378
Talisman!

28:10.381 --> 28:12.970
After 20 years

28:12.972 --> 28:15.372
of tithes and offerings

28:15.374 --> 28:17.041
and defending you,

28:17.043 --> 28:18.309
this is all you've got for me?

28:18.311 --> 28:19.610
A cat toy?

28:19.612 --> 28:21.979
And after all these years,

28:21.981 --> 28:24.548
you lost your faith?

28:24.550 --> 28:28.452
This is more about you

28:28.454 --> 28:30.354
than about me.

28:53.846 --> 28:56.046
"Who are you looking for?"

28:56.048 --> 28:58.983
Shine, Shine, Shine...

29:41.227 --> 29:43.093
Keep loading.

29:43.095 --> 29:45.295
I have something I need to take care of.

30:03.282 --> 30:05.482
Hailey!

30:05.484 --> 30:08.485
Hailey!

30:08.487 --> 30:11.088
Presents.

30:11.090 --> 30:13.123
What the?

31:56.796 --> 31:59.229
Sit up straight.

31:59.231 --> 32:02.332
Eat your vegetables.

32:02.334 --> 32:06.870
Put down that smartphone or tablet.

32:06.872 --> 32:09.239
The common refrain of the
typical American parent.

32:09.241 --> 32:11.408
Smoothie.

32:11.410 --> 32:13.677
Time to dance, bitch.

32:14.647 --> 32:17.281
Of course it does.

32:17.283 --> 32:18.749
But did you listen?

32:18.751 --> 32:20.918
No, you didn't,

32:20.920 --> 32:22.920
and now here we are.

32:22.922 --> 32:25.522
Starting today, your little lives

32:25.524 --> 32:28.125
will change in ways you
could never have imagined.

32:28.127 --> 32:30.027
There will be moments
when you will wonder

32:30.029 --> 32:32.696
what you have done to deserve these...

33:00.103 --> 33:01.869
Nightynight.

33:12.310 --> 33:13.491
What the hell is this?

33:13.494 --> 33:16.440
I saw you, you were just standing there,

33:16.443 --> 33:17.627
fingering yourself.

33:17.630 --> 33:19.651
Why is this truck still here?

33:19.653 --> 33:21.453
It's all loaded up, Mr. Scaramucci.

33:21.455 --> 33:22.588
We heard gunshots.

33:22.590 --> 33:23.589
Smoothie said that...

33:23.591 --> 33:25.557
Smoothie said?

33:25.559 --> 33:27.292
Smoothie...

33:27.294 --> 33:28.460
Where is he?

33:44.545 --> 33:46.578
Smile.

33:46.580 --> 33:48.747
Fuck you.

33:52.486 --> 33:54.653
I knew this day would come.

33:54.655 --> 33:57.823
Our destiny is in the stars.

33:57.825 --> 33:59.991
You do see that, Sax, don't you?

33:59.994 --> 34:01.927
You're not gonna ask
me my sign, are you?

34:01.929 --> 34:04.029
The universe, it conspired

34:04.031 --> 34:05.697
to bring us back together again

34:05.699 --> 34:08.867
so that a movable
object could finally meet

34:08.869 --> 34:11.054
irresistible force.

34:12.172 --> 34:13.572
Which one am I?

34:16.377 --> 34:17.743
The dumb one.

34:19.495 --> 34:23.882
Now, I have been thinking a lot lately

34:23.884 --> 34:27.719
about what I would do if
our paths ever crossed again.

34:27.721 --> 34:28.786
That makes two of us.

34:28.789 --> 34:30.355
See? See?

34:30.357 --> 34:33.292
It's destiny.

34:33.293 --> 34:35.460
Clearly,

34:35.463 --> 34:37.795
you are a man

34:37.797 --> 34:40.966
who must be broken.

34:40.967 --> 34:42.668
I am?

34:42.670 --> 34:45.204
But...

34:45.206 --> 34:48.318
What is pain to someone like you?

34:48.321 --> 34:51.389
What is death to someone like you?

34:51.391 --> 34:55.013
That is a very curious problem.

34:55.014 --> 34:56.248
Vexing.

34:56.250 --> 34:58.317
You have disarmed me, Sax.

34:58.319 --> 35:01.220
All of my usual weapons,
they just seem so inadequate.

35:01.222 --> 35:03.422
And my tried and true methods,

35:03.424 --> 35:05.324
they seem so...

35:05.326 --> 35:07.693
well...

35:07.695 --> 35:09.194
impotent.

35:09.196 --> 35:10.662
Torture, murder...

35:10.664 --> 35:11.697
They're hobbies.

35:11.699 --> 35:12.798
- Exactly.
- Yeah.

35:12.800 --> 35:15.868
All trifles to a man
who would cheerfully

35:15.870 --> 35:18.203
die in agony.

35:21.375 --> 35:23.842
I am going to show you something

35:23.844 --> 35:26.211
that I bet you never thought you'd see.

35:28.749 --> 35:33.185
I am going to show you
why they call me Smoothie.

35:33.187 --> 35:34.920
But I wasn't curious.

35:34.922 --> 35:36.421
Let's not do this.

35:36.423 --> 35:38.257
You don't need to do that, let's, no...

35:38.259 --> 35:39.691
Let's just put that right back on.

35:39.693 --> 35:41.093
- Just...
- Yeah, no.

35:41.095 --> 35:42.594
Aww, fuck me.

35:56.377 --> 35:58.810
Holy shit.

35:58.812 --> 36:00.646
Yikes, ugly lady.

36:00.648 --> 36:02.214
It's not nice to sneak up on people.

36:02.216 --> 36:03.749
Come on, I found Hailey.

36:03.751 --> 36:05.551
The bad guys are loading
the kids on a truck.

36:05.553 --> 36:07.505
Now, let's grab Nick
before it's too late.

36:07.508 --> 36:08.820
Where are you going?

36:08.822 --> 36:09.888
The wrong way, that's where.

36:09.890 --> 36:11.145
Nick is this way.

36:11.148 --> 36:12.661
I know because he believes in me,

36:12.664 --> 36:14.075
it's like a homing signal,

36:14.078 --> 36:15.369
llike in that movie,

36:15.372 --> 36:16.713
where the iguana phones home.

36:16.716 --> 36:18.497
Remember? Beep, beep, beep, beep.

36:21.602 --> 36:22.801
There we go.

36:24.271 --> 36:27.239
No, this way, this way, this way.

36:27.241 --> 36:29.608
Dumb as a soup sandwich.

36:32.479 --> 36:35.747
This way, this way.

36:35.749 --> 36:37.015
You're almost there, just...

36:37.017 --> 36:39.017
No, do...

36:39.019 --> 36:40.619
Yes, go, go, go, go!

36:49.330 --> 36:50.963
Are you cozy?

37:03.611 --> 37:05.177
Sax,

37:05.179 --> 37:07.045
relax.

37:15.322 --> 37:18.657
I am become destroyer of worlds!

37:18.659 --> 37:22.127
I will destroy your
world, you motherfucker!

37:22.129 --> 37:24.549
No!

37:24.552 --> 37:26.652
Yes! Yes!

37:26.655 --> 37:27.966
Damn you!

37:42.443 --> 37:44.516
Nick! Holy guacamole, Nick!

37:44.518 --> 37:45.817
That was close, buddy.

37:45.819 --> 37:47.096
We got here just...

37:47.099 --> 37:48.165
In the...

37:48.168 --> 37:51.269
In the nick of...

37:51.272 --> 37:53.558
Jelly beans.

37:57.907 --> 37:59.606
Get it out of me.

38:05.641 --> 38:07.341
Okay, take 'em.

38:19.622 --> 38:21.922
It's gone, the truck just left.

38:21.924 --> 38:23.157
It just left.

38:23.159 --> 38:24.958
Good boy, remember,

38:24.960 --> 38:26.994
those presents better be deliver...

38:26.996 --> 38:29.496
They'll be there!

38:52.888 --> 38:55.823
Mr. Scaramucci,

38:55.825 --> 38:57.524
are you all right?

39:02.064 --> 39:03.997
What am I?

39:06.869 --> 39:08.836
What the hell am I?

39:08.838 --> 39:10.504
You...

39:10.506 --> 39:12.306
You're the boss.

39:13.709 --> 39:16.810
I'm the boss of nothing.

39:16.812 --> 39:19.713
I'm...

39:19.715 --> 39:22.916
I'm an errand boy for psychopaths.

39:26.188 --> 39:29.156
Look, don't say that, Mr. Scaramucci.

39:35.431 --> 39:38.031
If I had that password...

39:39.768 --> 39:41.902
If I only had that goddamn passwo...

39:56.418 --> 39:58.952
Truck, Nick! The truck's getting away!

40:24.647 --> 40:26.213
Fuck.

41:05.020 --> 41:06.987
Hailey!

41:10.960 --> 41:12.926
Nick, hurry!

41:16.298 --> 41:17.798
Hailey!

41:17.800 --> 41:19.466
Hailey!

41:39.921 --> 41:42.822
We're too late, she's gone.

41:50.566 --> 41:53.054
Good, you two have met.

